text: Gd place for dinner with family. Reasonably priced standard dishes.
Tasty Assam Fish. Satay sauce has pineapple, authentic. The rojak has crispy beancurd.

Used to be a regular here until we moved out of the area, during the good old days cars were parked along the road. Glad to see that the food quality maintained, service is (lightning) fast and friendly. I love their Kam Heong fish head, has to be one of the best in Singapore.

Usually a pretty good place with good food. Bought sambal fried rice today but came extra 'ingredient'. Looks like baby centipede.

Threw away the entire packet of food.. Wasted.

$89 for 4 dishes and 3 rice.

Curry fish head: spicy and sour.

Salted egg prawns: my sister like it
